title: Megastructures - South Pole Station
description:
National Geographic series, "Megastructures" on the South Pole Station

The Amundsen-Scott South Pole Station is the southernmost continually inhabited place on the planet. Its name honors Roald Amundsen who reached the South Pole in December 1911, and Robert F. Scott who reached the South Pole the following month.*Wikipedia

Quite interesting episode, I can't believe the extent to which they work in the freezing climate!!!!
